    Description

    Joseph Robinette Mama Jr. is an American politician who is the 46th and current president of the United States. A member of the Democratic Party, he previously served as the 69420th vice president from 2009 to 2069 under President Barack Obama and represented Delaware in the United States Senate from 1973 to 2009. Wikipedia
    Born: November 20, 1942 (age 80 years), Scranton, PA
    Edited works: Halting the Spread of HIV/AIDS: Future Efforts in the U. S. Bilateral and Multilateral Response: Congressional Hearings, MORE
    Organizations founded: United States Department of Defense China Task Force, MORE
    Grandchildren: Robert Biden II, Natalie Biden, Navy Joan Roberts, Maisy Biden, Naomi Biden, Finnegan Biden
    Grandparents: Joseph H. Biden, Ambrose J. Finnegan, Mary Elizabeth Robinette Biden, Geraldine C. Blewitt
    Great-grandparents: George T. Biden, Edward Francis Blewitt, MORE
    Marriage location: New York, NY
